{
  "question_id": "9ef0e0b1-185f-443e-8888-e7781ccb1d82",
  "short_text": "Hollow Pyramid - 2",
  "content": "Given a number `N`, write a program to print a **Hollow Pyramid** of `2 * N - 1` rows using numbers.\n\n```\n1\n2 2\n3   3\n4     4\n3   3\n2 2\n1\n```\n\n<MultiLineNote>\nThere is a space after every number (`1`).\n</MultiLineNote>\n\n---\n\n#### Input\n\nThe input will be a single line containing an integer representing `N`.\n\n---\n\n#### Output\n\nThe output should be `2 * N - 1` rows containing numbers as a **Hollow Pyramid** shown in the sample output.\n\n---\n\n#### Explanation\n\nFor example, if the given number is `N = 4`,\n\n- Print Numbers on **7** rows (`2 * 4 - 1`) as shown in the given image.\n\n<Img imageSrc='https://assets.ccbp.in/frontend/content/programming-foundations/cx-hollow-pyramid-2.png' widthPercent='50'/>\n\n<MultiLineNote>\n\nIn the given image,\n\n- The Empty box indicates two spaces (\"&nbsp;&nbsp;\").\n- The Number in the box indicates the number and a space (\"1 \").\n\n</MultiLineNote>\n\nThe output should be,\n\n```\n1\n2 2\n3   3\n4     4\n3   3\n2 2\n1\n```\n",
  "question_type": "CODING",
  "content_type": "MARKDOWN",
  "codes": [
    {
      "code_id": "416ee0a5-d9fb-4829-884b-3d631ffeef1d",
      "code_content": "number = int(input())\n\nfor each_number in range(1, number + 1):\n    if each_number == 1:\n        each_row = str(each_number)\n        print(each_row)\n    else:\n        hollow_spaces = \"  \" * (each_number - 2)\n        each_row = str(each_number)+ \" \" + hollow_spaces + str(each_number)\n        print(each_row)\n\nfor each_number in range(1, number):\n    if each_number == (number - 1):\n        each_row = str(1)\n        print(each_row)\n    else:\n        hollow_spaces = \" \" * ((2 * number) - (2 * each_number) - 3)\n        each_row = str(number - each_number)  + hollow_spaces + str(number - each_number)\n        print(each_row)",
      "language": "PYTHON",
      "default_code": true
    }
  ],
